  <!-- Content -->
  <section
    class="mb-8 space-y-4 text-[#555555] dark:text-[#bbbbbb] leading-relaxed"
  >
    <!-- How to Write Date of Birth in Words -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-[#111111] dark:text-white">
      How to Write Date of Birth in Words?
    </h2>
    <p>
      Countries use different date formats: some use <a
        href="https://nirajkumar.space/dob/dobinfigures/"
        class="links">DD/MM/YYYY</a
      >, others use MM/DD/YYYY.
    </p>
    <p>You should use the correct date format according to your country.</p>

    <!-- Indian Format -->
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-[#111111] dark:text-white">
      How to Write Date of Birth in Words in Indian Format?
    </h3>
    <p>
      DD/MM/YYYY Format - Indian legal system use standard day/month/year
      format.
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc mb-2 space-y-2">
      <li>
        <strong>Day</strong> - Write day in ordinal numbers (First, Second, Third,
        etc.).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Month</strong> - Write the month in full format (January, February,
        March, etc).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Year</strong> - Write year in words using the cardinal numbers (2005
        → Two Thousand Five).
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mb-2">
      Example - 18 January 2024 → Eighteenth January, Two Thousand Twenty Four
    </p>
    <p class="text-red-400">
      Note: For years before 2000, ordinal numbers are used (1997 → Nineteen
      Hundred Ninety Seven).
    </p>

    <!-- British Format -->

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-[#111111] dark:text-white">
      How to Write Date of Birth in Words in British Format?
    </h3>
    <p>
      DD/MM/YYYY Format - British legal system use standard day/month/year
      format.
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc mb-2 space-y-2">
      <li>
        <strong>Day</strong> - Write the day in ordinal numbers (First, Second, Third,
        etc.), followed by 'the'.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Month</strong> - Write the month in full format (January, February,
        March, etc).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Year</strong> - Write year in words using the cardinal numbers (2007
        → Two Thousand and Seven).
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mb-2">
      Example - 18 January 2024 → The Eighteenth Of January, Two Thousand And
      Twenty Four
    </p>
    <p class="text-red-400">
      Note: Include the before cardinal day, and always include "and" between
      the year.
    </p>

    <!-- American Format -->
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-[#111111] dark:text-white">
      How to Write Date of Birth in Words in American Format?
    </h3>
    <p>MM/DD/YYYY Format - American legal system use month/day/year format.</p>
    <ul class="list-disc mb-2 space-y-2">
      <li>
        <strong>Month</strong> - Write the month in full format (January, February,
        March, etc).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Day</strong> - Write day in ordinal numbers (First, Second, Third,
        etc.).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Year</strong> - Write year in words using the cardinal numbers (20255
        → Two Thousand Twenty Five).
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Example - 18 January 2024 → January Eighteenth, Two Thousand Twenty Four
    </p>

    <!-- International Format -->
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-[#111111] dark:text-white">
      How to Write Date of Birth in Words in International Format?
    </h3>
    <p>
      DD/MM/YYYY Format - International system use standard day/month/year
      format.
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc mb-2 space-y-2">
      <li>
        <strong>Day</strong> - Write the day in ordinal numbers (First, Second, Third,
        etc.), followed by 'the'.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Month</strong> - Write the month in full format (January, February,
        March, etc).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Year</strong> - Write year in words using the cardinal numbers (2007
        → Two Thousand and Seven).
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mb-2">
      Example - 18 January 2024 → The Eighteenth Day Of January, Two Thousand
      And Twenty Four
    </p>
    <p class="text-red-400">
      Note: Include "the" before the day and "Day of" before the month.
    </p>

